speech.p:
I beg to present a Petition to this honourable House, signed by over 140,000 citizens of many races and religions in all parts of the United Kingdom. Your Petitioners emphasise in their Preamble that we live in a Commonwealth and country of divers religious and racial origins, and that no one can change either his ancestors or the colour of his skin through persuasion or propaganda. They therefore claim that incitement to hatred between racial groups is reprehensible because it leads to violence and humiliation, the loss of liberty and even the loss of life.
Wherefore your Petitioners pray that a law be enacted to make the public incitement of race hatred and discrimination an offence;
And your Petitioners, as in duty bound, will every pray.
